  "question": "<span class=\"TextRun  BCX8 SCXW96738212\" lang=\"EN-GB\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun  BCX8 SCXW96738212\"> According to Michael </span></span><span class=\"TextRun  BCX8 SCXW96738212\" lang=\"EN-GB\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun  BCX8 SCXW96738212\">Walzer</span></span><span class=\"TextRun  BCX8 SCXW96738212\" lang=\"EN-GB\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" data-contrast=\"auto\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun  BCX8 SCXW96738212\"> theory of justice which among the following equality must be applied?</span></span>",
  "option1": "Legal Equality",
  "option2": "Political Equality",
  "option3": "Simple Equality",
  "option4": "Complex Equality",
  "option5": "",
  "answer": "Complex Equality",
  "explanation": "<span data-contrast=\"auto\">The concept of complex equality was advocated by Michael W</span><span data-contrast=\"auto\">alzer</span><span data-contrast=\"auto\">. It held that a system of distribution should not contemplate equal distribution of same goods according to a uniform criterion but rather it should seek to ensure that inequalities in one sphere does not permeate into others.</span><span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233279&quot;:true,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\"> </span><br />\r\n<p><span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:360,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:259}\"> </span></p>"
